 the specialists and the hospitals.  The GEMS tender calls for businesses to bid for eight different types of contracts - an administrator; a clearing house; two providers of primary healthcare services ( for the \'93Sapphire\'94 and \'93Topaz\'94 options , which are 
described later on{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s14{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs28\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057\i0\b0 Both of these seem to be primary care options which allow for transfer of risk to the MCO. The differences between them are set out at transcript pages 1139-40}}}
